I need to identify the line item that represents capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares on the balance sheet.

Looking at the balance sheet, the line item "Paid-in Capital" represents the capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for company shares. This is the amount investors have paid to purchase shares of the company.

From the balance sheet:
- Initial Paid-in Capital: 16000000.00 as of 2023-12-31
- End Paid-in Capital: 16000000.00 as of 2024-02-03

The paid-in capital remained unchanged during this period, indicating there were no new share issuances or capital contributions during the reporting period.

```json
{"solution": {'initial value': '16000000.00', 'end value': '16000000.00'}}
```
